<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="33" pageId="2" pageNumber="31" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[140,1161,1337,1669]" pageId="2" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[179,304,1337,1362]" pageId="2" pageNumber="31">Diagnosis (</emphasis>
male). In the key to the males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1856" box="[656,767,1338,1362]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[656,767,1338,1362]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="31">Megaselia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the British Isles (
<bibRefCitation author="Disney" box="[1014,1153,1338,1362]" firstAuthor="Disney" pageId="2" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 155" refId="ref4577" refString="DISNEY R. H. L. 1989. Scuttle Flies - Diptera Phoridae Genus Megaselia. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insec ts 10 (8): 1 - 155. ISBN 0 901546 74 7." type="journal article" year="1989">Disney 1989</bibRefCitation>
) it runs to couplet 58, where neither option applies. However in such a case one is directed to proceed to couplet 92, where the hairs at the base of the hind femur are intermediate, but the species of the first option have different hypopygia. The second option leads on to couplets 136– 139, but all options have different hypopygia, as also with an additional six species not covered. In the key of 
<bibRefCitation author="Schmitz" box="[293,461,1491,1515]" firstAuthor="Schmitz" pageId="2" pageNumber="31" pagination="417 - 464" refId="ref4807" refString="SCHMITZ H. 1957. Phoridae. In: Lindner E (ed.), Die Fliegen der palaearktischen Region 4 (33), (Lieferung 196): 417 - 464. Stuttgart, E. Schweizerbart'sche Verlagsbuchhandlung." type="journal article" year="1957">Schmitz (1957)</bibRefCitation>
to the Palaearctic species of Abteilung II it runs to couplet 31, where neither option fits. It likewise it fails to key out in 
<bibRefCitation author="Borgmeier's" box="[743,954,1522,1546]" firstAuthor="Borgmeier's" pageId="2" pageNumber="31" pagination="257 - 416" refId="ref4427" refString="BORGMEIER T. 1964. Revision of the North American Phorid flies. Part II. The species of the genus Megaselia, subgenus Aphiochaeta (Diptera, Phoridae). Studia Entomologica, Petropolis 7: 257 - 416." type="journal article" year="1964">Borgmeier’s (1964)</bibRefCitation>
to Nearctic species of Group II; and likewise for the rest of the world fauna.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[140,1161,1337,1669]" lastBlockId="4.[140,1161,208,416]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="33" pageId="2" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[179,237,1583,1607]" pageId="2" pageNumber="31">Male</emphasis>
. Frons as 
<figureCitation box="[354,435,1583,1607]" captionStart="Figs 12–17" captionStartId="3.[140,177,1347,1366]" captionTargetBox="[146,1155,171,1326]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 12–17. Megaselia aulaeae n. sp. male. 12 – frons; 13 – postpedicels, palps and proboscis; 14 – mesopleuron; 15 – scvutellum; 16 – abdominal venter; 17 – left face of hypopygium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252438" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252438/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="31">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
, with very fine microtrichia mainly restricted to edges and by the median furrow. Cheek with 4 bristles and jowl with 2 that are much longer and more robust. Postpedicels, which lack SPS vesicles, palps and proboscis as 
<figureCitation box="[837,904,1645,1669]" captionStart="Figs 1–6" captionStartId="1.[139,176,1578,1597]" captionTargetBox="[146,1164,618,1536]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1–6. Gymnophora winqvisti Disney female. 1 – frons; 2 – postpedicels; 3 – palp; 4 – notopleuron; 5 – dorsal face of abdomen; 6 – tergite 7." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252430/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="31">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
. Thorax brown, with 3 notopleural bristles and no cleft in front of these. Mesopleuron with hairs and 2 bristles (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs 12–17" captionStartId="3.[140,177,1347,1366]" captionTargetBox="[146,1155,171,1326]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 12–17. Megaselia aulaeae n. sp. male. 12 – frons; 13 – postpedicels, palps and proboscis; 14 – mesopleuron; 15 – scvutellum; 16 – abdominal venter; 17 – left face of hypopygium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252438" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252438/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Scutellum with an anterior pair of small hairs and a posterior pair of bristles (
<figureCitation box="[1063,1146,1453,1477]" captionStart="Figs 12–17" captionStartId="3.[140,177,1347,1366]" captionTargetBox="[146,1155,171,1326]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 12–17. Megaselia aulaeae n. sp. male. 12 – frons; 13 – postpedicels, palps and proboscis; 14 – mesopleuron; 15 – scvutellum; 16 – abdominal venter; 17 – left face of hypopygium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252438" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252438/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
). Abdominal tergites brown with small hairs except at rear of T6 (
<figureCitation box="[867,950,1484,1508]" captionStart="Figs 12–17" captionStartId="3.[140,177,1347,1366]" captionTargetBox="[146,1155,171,1326]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 12–17. Megaselia aulaeae n. sp. male. 12 – frons; 13 – postpedicels, palps and proboscis; 14 – mesopleuron; 15 – scvutellum; 16 – abdominal venter; 17 – left face of hypopygium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252438" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252438/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
). Venter gray, and with hairs on segments 3–6 (
<figureCitation box="[462,546,1515,1539]" captionStart="Figs 12–17" captionStartId="3.[140,177,1347,1366]" captionTargetBox="[146,1155,171,1326]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 12–17. Megaselia aulaeae n. sp. male. 12 – frons; 13 – postpedicels, palps and proboscis; 14 – mesopleuron; 15 – scvutellum; 16 – abdominal venter; 17 – left face of hypopygium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252438" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252438/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
). Hypopygium as 
<figureCitation box="[751,876,1515,1539]" captionStart-0="Figs 12–17" captionStart-1="Figs 18–23" captionStartId-0="3.[140,177,1347,1366]" captionStartId-1="4.[140,177,1430,1449]" captionTargetBox-0="[146,1155,171,1326]" captionTargetBox-1="[146,1159,441,1401]" captionTargetPageId-0="3" captionTargetPageId-1="4" captionText-0="Figs 12–17. Megaselia aulaeae n. sp. male. 12 – frons; 13 – postpedicels, palps and proboscis; 14 – mesopleuron; 15 – scvutellum; 16 – abdominal venter; 17 – left face of hypopygium." captionText-1="Figs 18–23. Megaselia aulaeae n. sp. male. 18 – left hypandrial lobe and penis complex; 19 – right face of hypopygium; 20 – front tarsus; 21 – hind femur; 22 – base of hind femur; 23 – wing." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252438" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252442" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6252438/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6252442/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Figs 17–19</figureCitation>
), the left hypandrial lobe with long microtrichia and as 
<figureCitation box="[469,549,1545,1569]" captionStart="Figs 18–23" captionStartId="4.[140,177,1430,1449]" captionTargetBox="[146,1159,441,1401]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 18–23. Megaselia aulaeae n. sp. male. 18 – left hypandrial lobe and penis complex; 19 – right face of hypopygium; 20 – front tarsus; 21 – hind femur; 22 – base of hind femur; 23 – wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252442/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
. Legs brown except front leg with tip of coxa, tibia and tarsi yellowish. Fore tarsus with posterodorsal hair palisade on segments 1–4 and 5 clearly longer than 4 (
<figureCitation box="[301,384,1607,1631]" captionStart="Figs 18–23" captionStartId="4.[140,177,1430,1449]" captionTargetBox="[146,1159,441,1401]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 18–23. Megaselia aulaeae n. sp. male. 18 – left hypandrial lobe and penis complex; 19 – right face of hypopygium; 20 – front tarsus; 21 – hind femur; 22 – base of hind femur; 23 – wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252442/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
). Dorsal hair palisade of mid tibia extends about 0.67 times its length. Hairs below basal half of hind femur longer than those of anteroventral row of outer half differentiated posterodorsal hairs, without anterodorsals, and spinules of apical combs simple. Wings (
<figureCitation box="[227,308,239,263]" captionStart="Figs 18–23" captionStartId="4.[140,177,1430,1449]" captionTargetBox="[146,1159,441,1401]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 18–23. Megaselia aulaeae n. sp. male. 18 – left hypandrial lobe and penis complex; 19 – right face of hypopygium; 20 – front tarsus; 21 – hind femur; 22 – base of hind femur; 23 – wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252442/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity box="[325,424,239,263]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.33" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="1.33">1.33 mm</quantity>
long. Costal index 0.46. Costal cilia (of section 3) 
<quantity box="[1000,1160,239,263]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="9.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="0.095" valueMax="0.1" valueMin="0.09">0.09–0.10 mm</quantity>
long. No hair at base of vein 3. 2 unequal axillary bristles, the outermost being 
<quantity box="[1014,1097,269,293]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.1 mm</quantity>
long. Sc not reaching R1. Haltere brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
